why ```if(i > 0 && nums[i] == nums[i - 1] && used[i - 1] || used[i]) continue;``` can avoid duplicates?
For example, nums = [1,1,2]
We add the first 1 to the list, then we need to explore [1] + permutation of [1,2] (index 1 and 2)
When checking the second 1, if we don't check whether the first 1 has been used, then we will cexplore [1] + permutation of [1,2] (index 0 and 2)

