After doing `permutations i`, which I abstracted away with an `itertools` func, you should be able to wrap everything from there in a `set` and return in O(N) space
```
class Solution:
    def permuteUnique(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[List[int]]:
        def permute(nums: List[int]) -> List[List[int]]:
            return itertools.permutations(nums)
        p = permute(nums)
        s = set()
        for x in p:
            if x not in s:
                s.add(x)
        return s
```
which can be simplified to:
```py
return set(itertools.permutations(nums))
```

